name: Copernican Crater
description: Rim, wall and floor deposits of craters with sharp prominent rims, circular to polygonal outlines. High relative brightness and rays.
notes: n/a

name: Crater, Catena
description: Elongated linear clusters of overlapping circular to semi-circular.
notes: n/a

name: Copernican Crater, Secondary
description: Small to very small diameter craters, densely spaced near and/or on the ejecta blanket of craters.
notes: Impact crater forms derived from blocky material ejected from the primary impact.

name: Eratosthenian Crater
description: Non-rayed, circular craters with sharp to partially subdued crater rim crests, partial circumferential ejecta present, and lower albedo compared to unit Cc.
notes: Morphology and material from a primary impact event.

name: Eratosthenian Crater, Catena
description: Elongated linear to elliptical clusters of circular to semi-circular depressions, often overlapping.
notes: Impact crater clusters derived ejecta from large, basin forming impacts. Possibly primary impacts.

name: Eratosthenian Secondary Crater
description: Small to very small diameter craters, densely spaced near and/or on the ejecta blanket of craters.
notes: Impact crater forms derived from blocky material ejected from the primary impact.

name: Eratosthenian Mare
description: Low relative brightness plains with relatively few craters large enough to map, patches of small domes, sharp-crested ridges, observable flow fronts.
notes: Relatively thin, young volcanic flows or pyroclastic material.

name: Eratosthenian Imbrian Plateau
description: Forms high standing plateaus (relative to the mare surfaces in Oceanus Procellarum) with domes, cones, and dark mantling materials.
notes: Volcanic constructs, flows, and pyroclastic materials.

name: Imbrian Crater, Undivided
description: Subdued topographic relief compared to younger impact features, generally less than 40 km in diameter, with broad flat floors, and little to no ejecta present.
notes: Subdued morphology and material from a primary impact event.

name: Imbrian Crater, Lower
description: Similar description to unit Ic, craters mantled by materials of the Orientale group.
notes: Subdued morphology and material from a primary impact event, younger than Imbrium group materials but older than Orientale group materials.

name: Imbrian Crater, Upper
description: Similar description to unit Ic, craters superpose materials of the Orientale group.
notes: Subdued morphology and material from a primary impact event, younger than Orientale group materials but older than unit Im2.

name: Imbrian Crater, Catena
description: Subdued and mantled elongated linear to elliptical clusters of circular to semi-circular depressions, often overlapping.
notes: Impact crater clusters derived ejecta from large, basin forming impacts. Possibly primary impacts.

name: Imbrian Crater, Secondary
description: Small diameter craters, densely spaced near and/or on the ejecta blanket of craters.
notes: Impact crater forms derived from blocky material ejected from the primary impact.

name: Imbrian Crater, Fracture Floor
description: Crater floors typically domed, with furrows and/or linear to curvilinear fractures with variable widths and depths. Blocks and material between the fractures sometimes reoriented.
notes: Brittle materials uplifted and extended.

name: Imbrian Basin, Undivided
description: Gently rolling to hilly terrain containing aggregates of subdued irregular to circular craters. Also forms outer basin and ejecta of crater Schrodinger.
notes: Materials emplaced during the formation of multi-ringed impact basins.

name: Imbrian Basin, Massif
description: Rugged blocks forming arcuate raised ridges within crater Schrodinger.
notes: Material uplifted during basin formation, representing the inner ring of a multi-ringed impact basin.

name: Imbrian Dark Mantle
description: Some of the lowest albedo material mapped, generally occurs near the outer margins of larger basins. Scalloped, smooth textures with small craters.
notes: Pyroclastic material.

name: Imbrian Grooved
description: Covers craters and other terrae of pre-Nectarian through Imbrian age. Craters have radial grooves on rims and walls with some mounds.
notes: Origin uncertain. Possibly Imbrium ejecta or result of seismic shaking.

name: Imbrian Imbrium Alpes Formation
description: Angular blocky and knobby with smooth, mantled surface. Closely spaced hills and hummocks, ~2-5 km in diameter.
notes: Possibly eroded ejecta, structurally deformed bedrock, or both.

name: Imbrian Imbrium Apenninus Formation
description: Coarse blocks of material parallel to scarp bordering Imbrium basin. Smooth to undulating interblock materials.
notes: Intensely fractured bedrock with interstitial Imbrium ejecta.

name: Imbrian Imbrium Crater
description: Individual craters <25 km diam., clusters and chains of craters <10 km diam. radial to Imbrium. Moderately subdued topographic features.
notes: Secondaries and crater chains emplaced during Imbrium basin formation.

name: Imbrian Imbrium Fra Mauro Formation
description: Sinuous, curvilinear, and straight ridges draping the surface below. Surface texture locally hummocky.
notes: Ejecta from Imbrium basin and materials of the substrate.

name: Imbrian Mare, Lower
description: Forms flat, smooth surfaces. Relatively higher albedo compared to unit Im2 but lower albedo than unit Ip. High density of superposed craters.
notes: Old basaltic lava, perhaps as old as Orientale basin.

name: Imbrian Mare, Upper
description: Forms flat, smooth surfaces. Lower albedo and crater density than unit Im1. Numerous ridges. Difficult to distinguish from unit Id.
notes: Basaltic lava flows.

name: Imbrian Mare, Dome
description: Steeply sloping, high-relief, rough domical or conical shaped edifices, sometimes with pitted summits.
notes: Volcanic edifices or laccoliths

name: Imbrian Orientale Hevelius Formation, Inner Facies
description: Curvilinear to swirly ridges and troughs mostly radial and subradial to Orientale basin.
notes: Continuous ejecta blanket emplaced during outward flow of hot, turbulent, mobile materials.

name: Imbrian Orientale Hevelius Formation, Outer Facies
description: Swirly, lineated, hummocky and smooth materials forming a discontinuous and irregular boundary.
notes: Thinning distal margins of Orientale basin ejecta.

name: Imbrian Orientale Hevelius Formation, Secondary Crater Facies
description: Overlapping crater chains and clusters radial and peripheral to the basin.
notes: Secondary impact craters formed by ejected blocks.

name: Imbrian Orientale Maunder Formation
description: Smooth to rolling, intensely fractured plains with broad linear ridges and smooth domes.
notes: Mostly impact melt. Ridges and domes likely original floor material modified through compression.

name: Imbrian Orientale Montes Rook Formation, Knobby Facies
description: Knobby, hummocky, rolling and chaotic materials with interstitial irregular grooves and depressions.
notes: Uppermost part of overturned flap of the ejecta sequence of Orientale basin.

name: Imbrian Orientale Montes Rook Formation, Massif Facies
description: High-relief, smooth blocks marking the second and third rings of the basin.
notes: Structurally uplifted bedrock, thickly veneered with late arriving ejecta.

name: Imbrian Plains
description: Smooth, flat to undulatory terrain of intermediate albedo occurring mostly in topographic lows and crater floors of Imbrian and older age.
notes: Ambiguous origin, likely Orientale and other large impact crater ejecta.

name: Imbrian Terra
description: Low relief, low crater density, moderate to high albedo, moderately smooth surface.
notes: Complex mixture of local erosional debris and crater and basin ejecta; megaregolith.

name: Imbrian Terra, Dome
description: Outlines and characteristics similar to main-sequence craters, with smooth inner flanks, paucity of ejecta, inner terracing, secondary cratering.
notes: Possibly target material differences, or ash-flow calderas.

name: Imbrian Nectarian Plains
description: Smooth, flat to undulating surface, moderate to high density of superposed craters.
notes: Possibly materials emplaced by the formation of Imbrian and Nectarian basins.

name: Imbrian Nectarian Terra
description: Gently rolling terrain, moderate to high density of craters.
notes: Complex mixture of local erosional debris and crater and basin ejecta; megaregolith.

name: Nectarian Crater
description: Considerably muted topographic relief compared to younger impact features, with broad flat floors typically another unit, and very little to no ejecta present.
notes: Muted morphology and material from a primary impact event.

name: Nectarian Basin, Undivided
description: Material of raided walls and slumped blocks of basins, as well as aggregates of closely spaced subdued hills and ridges.
notes: Impact related structures and ejecta material.

name: Nectarian Basin, Lineated
description: Sharp, raised ridges, intervening flat areas or deep troughs and smooth hills with narrow grooves.
notes: Bedrock pervasively faulted by Imbrium impact.

name: Nectarian Basin, Massif
description: Rugged blocks most commonly 10 to 30 km across, forms highest and most rugged parts of arcuate raised ridges.
notes: Uplifted bedrock during the formation of Nectarian basins.

name: Nectarian Basin, Secondary Crater
description: Grouped in clusters, chains and groove-like chains, mostly peripheral and approximately radial to Nectarian basins.
notes: Secondary impact craters of Nectarian basins.

name: Nectarian Nectaris Janssen Formation
description: Rolling subdued terrain having numerous linear features including ridges, scarps, and grooves radial to Nectaris basin.
notes: Nectaris basin ejecta equivalent to, but more degraded than, units Iif, Iohi, and Ioho.

name: Nectarian Plains
description: Generally flat, moderate albedo terrain with dense population of large, old craters.
notes: Ambiguous origin, possible ejecta from large impacts and basin forming events.

name: Nectarian Terra
description: Moderately rough surface, rolling to moderately rugged overall relief, with diverse ages of superposed and buried craters.
notes: Complex mixture of local erosional debris and crater and basin ejecta; megaregolith.

name: Nectarian Terra-Mantling and Plains
description: Light colored, wavy or rolling surfaces more heavily cratered than unit Ip.
notes: Primary and secondary ejecta of Nectarian basins and large craters equivalent to units Ioho

name: pre-Nectarian Basin
description: Subdued, eroded mountain rings and arcuate segments of rings, rim, walls, and inner-ring materials.
notes: Erosionally degraded impact related structures and ejecta materials.

name: pre-Nectarian Basin Massif
description: Large mountainous landforms commonly lying along arc, both continuous and discontinuous, gradational with generally finer-scale topography.
notes: Uplifted bedrock during the formation of basins.

name: pre-Nectarian Crater
description: Discontinuous, subdued rim crests and rounded, curved or straight rim remnants.
notes: Erosionally degraded morphology and material from a primary impact event.

name: pre-Nectarian Terra
description: Rugged, diverse terrain, degraded partial crater rims, gradational with smoother unit Nt, and rougher units pNbm and pNc.
notes: Complex mixture of local erosional debris and crater and basin ejecta; megaregolith.
